Hungary’s Cabinet to Discuss Mortgage Plan Today, Nemzet Reports

-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 
2011-05-24T06:09:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/hungary-s-cabinet-to-discuss-mortgage-plan-today-nemzet-reports.html
Hungary’s government will discuss
planned measures to assist distressed mortgage holders at a
cabinet meeting today,  Magyar Nemzet  reported, citing government
spokeswoman Anna Nagy.  The Economy Ministry and the  Banking Association  may sign
the agreement today if the government approves the plan, the
newspaper reported.  A detailed announcement of the measures may only come later
in the week, the Budapest-based newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
